[assistant] Fixed `AnnotationBuilderTest` to avoid the JVM failure from Morphia’s optional CGLIB lazy-proxy initialization.
[assistant] 
[assistant] Change made in:
[assistant] 
[assistant] - `tests/src/org.mongodb.morphia/morphia/1.3.2/src/test/java/org_mongodb_morphia/morphia/AnnotationBuilderTest.java`
[assistant] 
[assistant] What changed:
[assistant] 
[assistant] - Before creating `Morphia`, the test now disables Morphia’s optional lazy proxy support by setting `LazyFeatureDependencies.fulFilled` to `false`.
[assistant] - This prevents CGLIB from trying to reflectively open `ClassLoader#defineClass`, which fails on modern JDKs without `--add-opens`.
[assistant] 
[assistant] I did not run the tests locally per workflow instructions.
[assistant-event] text_end
